# Example Wrangler local dev variables for apps/api-worker
#
# Wrangler will read a local .dev.vars file (not committed) when running `wrangler dev`.
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` and fill values you actually intend to use.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Do not commit `.dev.vars`.
# - The web UI does not use client-baked tokens.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A: legacy token mode (API-only dev/test)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# APERION_AUTH_MODE=token
# API_TOKEN=your-secure-token-here
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B: Access mode (matches production shape)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# APERION_AUTH_MODE=access
# CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=yourteam.cloudflareaccess.com   # or just the team slug
# CF_ACCESS_AUD=your-access-aud                         # comma-separated allowed
#
# Optional: allow service-token auth (for probes/automation)
# CF_ACCESS_SERVICE_TOKEN_ID=...
# CF_ACCESS_SERVICE_TOKEN_SECRET=...
